&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Company&amp;nbsp;Overview&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;335557856&amp;quot;:16777215,&amp;quot;335559738&amp;quot;:150,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:150,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:300}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;ClearView Healthcare Partners is a premier life sciences strategy consulting firm headquartered in Boston, with offices in San Francisco, New York City, London, Zurich and Gurgaon. Serving clients in the biopharmaceutical, medical device, and diagnostic spaces, we provide world-class strategic decision-making support across a diverse range of business issues. Our goal is to inform actionable recommendations that allow companies to achieve their business objectives.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;At ClearView, you will encounter an entrepreneurial environment, interact with a dynamic group of colleagues, present to clients in critical business situations, and develop a deep understanding of the life sciences and biopharmaceutical industry. You will be mentored directly by ClearView managers, who have a wealth of experience in life sciences consulting. In addition, you will be exposed to a wide variety of business issues including new product planning, pricing &amp;amp; market access, investor services, launch and product commercialization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will interact with both clients and teams within ClearView to address critical strategic questions within the biopharmaceutical space. Initially, your work will span multiple projects supporting targeted activities which may be different across each project. Those activities include the following:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct complex problem-solving through a hypothesis-based approach&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create templated outputs to support overall project deliverable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to conduct a straightforward project or workstream with moderate oversight&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and utilize analytic tools (e.g., forecast models) to support key decision-making&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate recommendations to clients to inform strategy and maximize value&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At ClearView, you will have the opportunity to refine a broad range of expertise, skills, and connections that will heighten your career.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful life sciences consultant candidate must have the following skills and experience:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to independently manage activities across multiple workstreams (e.g., storylines, ghosting documents, data gathering, etc.), and able to provide thought partnership for more ambiguous or complex projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written and oral communication skills in English&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Well-positioned to serve as a mentor for junior team members&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enthusiasm for working in a dynamic, fast-paced, and collaborative team environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in Microsoft Office Suite (e.g. Outlook, Excel, PowerPoint, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Requires and seeks support for more complex projects or difficult client situations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly analytical and structured approach to solving complex problems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Undergraduate or Master’s degree in the life sciences or equivalent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of three years of experience in life sciences consulting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrates curiosity about business and healthcare strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicates clearly in both written and oral settings&lt

